#extract POP variables from the studypop data frame
my.x <- names(studypop)[grep("la", names(studypop))] 

#create a new data frame with my.x and convert values for the predictor variables to its natural log.
log.x <- data.frame(apply(studypop[,my.x], 2, FUN = function(x) log(x))) %>%
  setNames(paste(my.x, "l2", sep = ".")) %>% #add suffix 12 to the predictors' name
  na.omit() #remove missing

Heat Map

cormat <- round(cor(studypop[grep("la", names(studypop))], use = "pairwise.complete.obs", method = c("spearman")),2)
melted_cormat <- melt(cormat) %>% rename(Correlation = value)

melted_cormat <- melted_cormat %>% 
  mutate(group3.1 = case_when(Var1 == "lbx118la" ~ "TEQ",
                           grepl("lbxf|d", Var1) == TRUE ~ "TEQ",
                           grepl("lbx1|0", Var1) == TRUE ~ "Non-Dioxin-like PCB",
                           grepl("lbxh|p", Var1) == TRUE ~ "Non-Ortho PCB")) %>% 
  mutate(group3.2 = case_when(Var2 == "lbx118la" ~ "TEQ",
                           grepl("lbxf|d", Var2) == TRUE ~ "TEQ",
                           grepl("lbx1|0", Var2) == TRUE ~ "Non-Dioxin-like PCB",
                           grepl("lbxh|p", Var2) == TRUE ~ "Non-Ortho PCB")) %>% 
  mutate(Var1 = fct_recode(Var1, "PCB 74" = "lbx074la",
                                "PCB 99" = "lbx099la",
                                "PCB 118" = "lbx118la",
                                "PCB 138" = "lbx138la",
                                "PCB 153" = "lbx153la",
                                "PCB 170" = "lbx170la",
                                "PCB 180" = "lbx180la",
                                "PCB 187" = "lbx187la",
                                "PCB 194" = "lbx194la",
                                "1,2,3,6,7,8-hxcdd" = "lbxd03la",
                                "1,2,3,4,6,7,8-hpcdd" = "lbxd05la",
                               "1,2,3,4,6,7,8,9-ocdd" =  "lbxd07la",
                               "2,3,4,7,8-pncdf" =  "lbxf03la",
                               "1,2,3,4,7,8-hxcdf" =  "lbxf04la",

         Var2 = fct_recode(Var2, "PCB 74" = "lbx074la",
                                "PCB 99" = "lbx099la",
                                "PCB 118" = "lbx118la",
                                "PCB 138" = "lbx138la",

                               "1,2,3,4,6,7,8,9-ocdd" =  "lbxd07la",

                               "1,2,3,4,6,7,8-hxcdf" =  "lbxf08la",
                               "PCB 169" =  "lbxhxcla",
                                "PCB 126" = "lbxpcbla"))

melted_cormat %>% 
  mutate(Var1 = fct_relevel(Var1, "PCB 194", after = 8),
         Var2 = fct_relevel(Var2, "PCB 194", after = 8),
         Var1 = fct_relevel(Var1, "PCB 118", after = 8),
         Var2 = fct_relevel(Var2, "PCB 118", after = 8)) %>% 
ggplot(aes(Var1, Var2, fill = Correlation)) +
 geom_tile(color = "white") +
 scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", 
                      midpoint = 0, limit = c(0,1), space = "Lab", 
                      name = "Spearman\nCorrelation") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 15) + # minimal theme
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 1, size = 12, hjust = 1),
        axis.text.y = element_text(vjust = 1, size = 12, hjust = 1),
        axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size = 15)) +
  coord_fixed() + labs(x = "", y = "")

melted_cormat %>% 
 mutate(group3.1 = fct_relevel(group3.1, c("TEQ", "Non-Ortho PCB", "Non-Dioxin-like PCB"))) %>% 
 ggplot(aes(Var1, Var2, fill = Correlation)) +
 geom_tile(color = "white") +
 scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", 
                      midpoint = 0, limit = c(0,1), space = "Lab", 
                      name = "Spearman\nCorrelation ") +
  scale_x_discrete(expand = c(0, 0)) + 
  scale_y_discrete(expand = c(0, 0)) + theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1),
        panel.spacing = unit(0, "lines"),
        panel.border = element_rect(colour = "black", size=0.7),
        strip.placement = "outside", 
        legend.position = "bottom",
        strip.background = element_rect(fill = "white")) +
  labs(x = "", y = "") +
  facet_grid(group3.2 ~ group3.1, scales = "free", space = "free",
             labeller = labeller(group3.1 = label_wrap_gen(5),
                                 group3.2 = label_wrap_gen(5)))

  }

Visualization of Hierarchical clustering N = 3

Means of the pollutants in each cluster compare to the mean of the chemicals in the entired population to identified in which clusters individuals are located based on exposure. We see that in cluster 1, we find individuals that have means of chemical higher than the chemical mean in the entire population. In the case of cluster 2, most of the observations within this cluster very similar chemical concentrations to the mean of the chemical in the entire popullation. In the third cluster, we see that most of the individuals within this cluster have chemical means below the chemical means of the entire population.

hc3.cl <- aggregate(as.matrix(log.x) ~ as.factor(hc.clusters.3), data = hc_health_3, FUN = mean)[,-1]
 
hc3.cl <- as.data.frame.matrix(t(hc3.cl))
hc3.cl$chem <- row.names(hc3.cl)
 
means_hc3 <- hc3.cl %>%
  mutate(Group = ifelse(chem == "lbx118la.l2", "TEQ",
                        ifelse(grepl("lbx1", chem), "Non-Dioxin-like PCB",
                               ifelse(grepl("lbx0", chem), "Non-Dioxin-like PCB",
                                      ifelse(grepl("lbxp", chem), "Non-Ortho PCB",
                                             ifelse(grepl("lbxh", chem), "Non-Ortho PCB", "TEQ"))))))
 
plot_means_hc3 <- means_hc3 %>%
  rename("Cluster 3" = V1, "Cluster 2" = V2, "Cluster 1" = V3) %>% 
  gather(key = "Cluster", value = "mean", -chem, -Group) %>% as.tibble()
 
plot_chem_means %>% as.tibble() %>% rename(pop_mean = `colMeans(log.x)`) %>%
  right_join(., plot_means_hc3, by = c("Group", "chem")) %>%
